				<td colspan="2"><span>As said above, changing your resists has no effect on the success or failure of spells you cast.  In hard LDON, the lull resist rate is just stupidly high.  They clearly did not intend for people to use lull consistently on hard.  I think a 50% success rate might actually be higher than my experience.  I rely more on lull and fade techniques to win hard LDONs.  Crowd control, not lulling, is the key.</span></td>
