			</tr>
		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: problems lulling in hard ldon<a name="23152"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 23 04 11:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;really need advice here 
<br />
currently running with 250 cha,IM2,SM2, JF2 and epic. i bring up vesshan to raise my magic resistance up and still have about 50% resists on lulls. i have tried amping my voice also but still seem to have problems lulling even dark blues. &quot;
<br />

<br />
IM2, SM2, epic, POV, and Amp will not affect your resist rates on Lull.  IM, SM, epic, and Amp affect the modifier applied to determine effectiveness of songs, which does not affect resist rates.
<br />

<br />
It's an open question whether JF2 does or doesn't.  Best evidence seems to suggest JF works like IM &amp; SM, in that it raises your effective level only for purposes of computing the effectiveness of a song -- e.g., more DS, more mana from Marr, etc. -- but does not raise your effective level for purposes of computing resists.  But, AFAIK nobody has proven either way for sure.
<br />

<br />
POV, as prior posters have made clear, has no effect on lull landing.
<br />

<br />

<br />
CHA is relevant to computing chances of a critical fail.  Comparative level and mob's MR are all that matter for determining chance of an initial resist.  So pump your CHA up all you can, use lull only when you really need it, and be ready to try several times. 
<br />

<br />
&quot;currently thinking of getting more FT items and raising my mana supply to charm/fade pull &quot;
<br />

<br />
I am assuming you are doing level 65 hards.  On that assumption, you will be unable to charm anything that matters.  If you mean mez/fade, yes -- that's the correct thing to do.
<br />

<br />

<br />
There are numerous threads here and on Concert Hall about how to pull hard LDONs.  Search is your friend.  Two things I can add that don't come across clearly in most of them.
<br />

<br />
1.  You'll be surprised at how effective proximity agro can be for getting single pulls.  Try it.  Try it with DA on also.
<br />

<br />
2.  Don't forget to make liberal use of the toggle last two targets key.  Snag two targets first, then mez, run, toggle, mez on the run, fade, etc.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
