				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: problems lulling in hard ldon<a name="23165"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 23 04 12:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>lull just is not worth the time. I have noticed that our mez on hard adventures hardly ever fails and my cha is usually near 186 with out buff.  I find that using mez as an aggro setter while giving yourself a lot of room to run backwards affords you time to retarget the chase mobs, cast another mez to distance mobs if there are 3 or to fade if there are more than 3.   I like to bring one to camp and wait for my mez off message to hit.  I then wait for it to come debuff at max range and remez till first mob dead, or to fade once mez message drops.  BE ADVISED  if you fade with mobs mezzed then go back to camp with the remains, YOU HAVE NOT LOST AGGRO on the mezzed mob. Nice thing bout the 1 min mez is that with a good group on hard missions, you get a perfect spread time. I always chain pull / park on hard missions. that gives all classes a chance to do thier part on slow/debuff and there is never any down time. I hardly ever get more than two mobs with just proximity in the halls.  Big rooms are always easily broken with the mez trick.</span></td>
