				<td colspan="2"><span>What I like to do is lull as many as I can.  If I get a resist, snare your current target, then gate the other mobs and fade.  As long as you have enough room to work, this will work fine.  Some mobs can't be lulled from what I have been told, so you just have to get a feel for which mobs can and can't be.  If there are several mobs to pick from and only 1 cons even, try lulling the others since most of the lvl 65 mobs will resist the lull.  I usually have around 250 cha when buffed, and there is a huge difference in resists between 200 cha and 250 cha, with both lulls and mezzes.  So don't forget to get a cha buff before adv.</span></td>
