			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: problems lulling in hard ldon<a name="23747"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 9:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have also read a number of posts of people who say that FM code is bugged.  Several state they can easily replicate the bug.
<br />

<br />
I have tried what they described, and the bug does not seem to affect me at all.
<br />

<br />
I have no explanation for why this is.  Couple possibilities suggest themselves, though:
<br />

<br />
1.  It genuinely is a bug, but one that only affects some people.  EQ's code is complex enough that I could easily see something creeping in that is only a problem if you're a particular race, or have particular stats, or wear particular gear or whatever.  In SwG, some people had a bug that let them summon multiple pets, while others didn't.  No discernable rhyme nor reason--just somewhere in the bowels of the code, some variable was off.
<br />

<br />
2.  It's not really a bug, it's one of these things we know makes fade fail, and people just don't know they're doing it.  Maybe they're leaving a hostile song playing.  Maybe the mob sees inviso.  Etc. etc.  A lot of apparently quite competent people are reporting such a bug, so I'm less inclined to believe this explanation.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Seems like the moral is:  if it happens to you once, worry that it might happen again.  But if you're not noticing a problem with this, no need to start worrying now.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
