				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: problems lulling in hard ldon<a name="24318"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 27 04 3:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The 65 mez is NOT 1 minute.  None of our mezzes lasts 1 minute.  I THINK the person who said that was referring to the level 64 charm song.  For the record, after you hit around an average level of 62 or 63 in your adventures, you aren't charming anything in them anyway.  No, the level 65 mez has a roughly 15 second duration like all other mezzes.  The good things about it are 1) No knockback/forward effect and 2) Enormous range.  I would recommend FT5 plus MC1 for hard, though I have done hard LDONs where I only faded 2 or 3 times the entire dungeon.  Mobs at level 65 hit for 990 max and they will definitely double for a pair of 990s on a pull fairly easily.  You can pull 3 and mez 2, but staying alive until you get two of them mezzed may be difficult.  My goal 99% of the time is to pull 2 mobs on each pull.</span></td>
